- ts: 2026-04-10T00:00:00Z
  event: clarify_critic
  feature: document-claude-config-dir-direnv-pattern-for-per-repo-permissions-scoping
  findings:
    - "The research DR-7 says 'hot = pause the per-repo permissions work' while the ticket says 'hot = ship docs as interim workaround.' These contradict — DR-7 instructs to pause, the ticket instructs to always ship. Intent clarity's HIGH rating buries a live contradiction."
    - "The hot-outcome branch in the ticket narrows DR-7's three-way branch (quiet/warm/hot → proceed/size-for-retirement/pause) into a two-way branch (ship regardless, tone varies). Requirement drift the Intent assessment should have flagged."
    - "In-scope list uses hedging language ('likely docs/per-repo-permissions.md or similar', 'if one exists', 'or a just launch recipe variant') — scope-expansion vectors glossed over by the HIGH Scope boundedness rating."
    - "Defense-in-depth requirement is about global settings.json template being conservative. Docs teaching users to swap the entire user scope per repo is orthogonal — users can create a more-permissive shadow settings.json, which sits in tension with defense-in-depth without a direct conflict. Alignment cited without addressing the tension."
    - "Graceful partial failure dismissed as n/a for docs. Shadow mechanism introduces silent drift failure modes (stale skills/hooks/statusline) across all user-facing infrastructure — shipping a mechanism in docs still ships the mechanism."
    - "Criticality=medium misreads risk. Docs recommending cp -r shadowing of the entire user scope can cause silent infrastructure drift across all skills and hooks. The default for skill/lifecycle/hook/workflow changes is high."
    - "Ticket devotes significant wordcount to re-arguing DR-8's 10 failure modes in its own body — scope seepage, suggests the author had not fully settled on closing Option D."
    - "'Iterative improvement' requirement is about architecture tolerating exploratory development, not about deferring tooling until users complain. Citation laundered decomposition heuristic as requirement alignment."
    - "Direnv docs and shell-alias fallbacks sit on the boundary of requirements/project.md's out-of-scope 'Dotfiles and machine configuration' clause — whether these docs belong in cortex-command or machine-config is not settled in the source."
  dispositions:
    apply: 3
    dismiss: 5
    ask: 1
  applied_fixes:
    - "Edited research.md DR-7 and backlog/065 body to resolve the hot-outcome contradiction in favor of a ship-minimal-under-hot framing. Research legacy 'pause' language is now explicitly noted as superseded by the collapsed docs-only plan."
    - "Downgraded Requirements alignment from HIGH to 'Partial alignment' — noting the defense-in-depth tension (shadow scopes can be more permissive than global) without treating it as a conflict."
    - "Upgraded Criticality from medium to high — docs instructing users to cp -r shadow the entire user scope can cause silent infrastructure drift across all skills/hooks, matching the default for skill/lifecycle/hook/workflow-affecting changes."
  status: ok

